<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad">
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="main">
      <h1>Translation groups</h1>
      <p>
        A <dfn>translation group</dfn> is a set of teams or individual
        supervisors chosen by the owner of a distribution, project group, or
        project to manage its translations.
        Each team or supervisor in a group is responsible for one or more
        specific languages.
      </p>
      <p>
        Where contributions are &ldquo;Structured&rdquo; or
        &ldquo;Restricted,&rdquo; members of the translation group have
        the final say on translations in their languages.  Where
        contributions are &ldquo;Closed,&rdquo; only members of the
        translation group can translate at all.
      </p>
      <table class="sortable listing" id="translation-groups" width="100%">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Translation Group</th>
            <th>Supervises Translations for</th>
            <th>Created</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr tal:repeat="group context">
            <td>
              <a
                tal:content="group/title/fmt:shorten/57"
                tal:attributes="href group/name"
              >title</a>
            </td>
            <td>
              <span tal:condition="group/distributions" tal:omit-tag="">
                <span tal:repeat="distro group/distributions" tal:omit-tag="">
                  <span tal:replace="distro/name">ubuntu</span>,
                </span>
              </span>
              <span tal:condition="group/projects" tal:omit-tag="">
                <span tal:repeat="project group/projects" tal:omit-tag="">
                  <span tal:replace="project/name">gnome</span>,
                </span>
              </span>
              <span tal:condition="group/products" tal:omit-tag="">
                <span tal:repeat="product group/products" tal:omit-tag="">
                  <span tal:replace="product/name">a52dec</span>,
                </span>
              </span>
            </td>
            <td>
              <span class="sortkey"
                tal:content="group/datecreated/fmt:datetime" />
              <span
                tal:attributes="title group/datecreated/fmt:datetime"
                tal:content="group/datecreated/fmt:approximatedate">
                2007-08-15
              </span>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <ul class="menu">
        <tal:can-edit condition="context/required:launchpad.Admin">
          <li class="add">
            <a href="+new">Add a new translation group</a>
          </li>
        </tal:can-edit>
      </ul>
    </div><!--main-->
    <div metal:fill-slot="help">
      <p>
        These translation groups are available to help translate software to
        various languages.  A group may help on any number of projects, and
        be capable of translating into one or more languages.
      </p>
      <p>
        A translation group is generally expected to work together with some
        degree of coordination.  Some translation groups may exist to translate
        particular classes of application, others may focus on specific language
        families.  A translation group may even start as an arbitrary circle of
        friends.  It is often easier to assign a translation group to work on a
        project as a single entity with its own membership management, than to
        keep track of individual translators on every project the group works
        on.
      </p>
      <ul class="info">
        <li>
          <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/RosettaFAQ"
          >Frequently asked questions</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
